'''''Alhokm Baad Almozawla''''' ([[Arabic]]:الحكم بعد المزاولة) (variously translated as "Judgment After a Prank", "Judgement after Deliberations" and "The Verdict After Judgment") is a popular Egyptian [[hidden camera]]/[[practical joke]] [[Reality television#Hidden cameras|reality]] [[television series]]. On the show, unsuspecting celebrities are under the pretense that they are being interviewed for an Arabic-speaking German TV network. They are asked about their views on [[Israel]], and then told they are on Israeli TV, provoking a range of reactions.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://thedailynewsegypt.com/2012/07/29/prank-programme-stirs-further-tv-based-political-controversy/|title=Prank program stirs further TV based political controversy |newspaper=Daily News Egypt|date=29 July 2012|accessdate=12 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/world/prank-tv-show-exposes-egypts-anti-israel-anger/story-fnd12peo-1226443066314|title=Prank TV show exposes Egypt's anti-Israel anger |newspaper=Courier Mail|date=5 August 2012|accessdate=12 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/08/10/world/africa/egyptian-prank-show/index.html?hpt=hp_t3|title=Egyptian prank show exposes anti-Israeli sentiment |newspaper=CNN|date=11 August 2012|accessdate=12 August 2012}}</ref>
