The '''Bletonesii''' were one of the pre-[[Ancient Rome|Roman]] [[Celt]]ic peoples of the [[Iberian Peninsula]] (the Roman [[Hispania]], modern [[Spain]] and [[Portugal]]), dwelling around the city of ''Bletisa'' or ''Bletisama'', located in modern [[Ledesma, Salamanca|Ledesma]] in the [[province of Salamanca]], Spain.<ref>[[Conrad Cichorius]], ''Römische Studien'' (Berlin, 1922)</ref> They were punished by the Romans for practicing human sacrifice.<ref>[http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Roman_Questions*/D.html#ref187 ''Quaestiones Romanes''], question 83</ref> If the placement in Bletisa is correct, they lived near (or they were part of) the [[Vettones]].

