'''The Children of Violence''' is a series of five semi-autobiographical novels by British [[Nobel Prize in Literature]]-winner [[Doris Lessing]]: ''[[Martha Quest]]'' (1952), ''[[A Proper Marriage]]'' (1954), ''[[A Ripple from the Storm]]'' (1958), ''[[Landlocked (novel)|Landlocked]]'' (1965), and ''[[The Four-Gated City]]'' (1969).<ref name="jacket">From [http://www.dorislessing.org/thecity.html the dust jacket of the first edition] of ''The Four-Gated City''.</ref>
The series follows the life of the protagonist Martha Quest from adolescence until her death, which takes place in the future, in the year 1997. The first four novels are set during the 1930s and 1940s, in the former [[British Colony#History|British colony]] of [[Southern Rhodesia]], now [[Zimbabwe]], in southern Africa, where Lessing lived from 1925 until 1949.<ref>[http://www.dorislessing.org/biography.html DorisLessing.org]</ref> The fifth work, ''The Four-Gated City'', is a science fiction [[dystopia]] set in [[London]], from the 1950s into a future where World War Three takes place.
