'''Fabrice Desvignes''' is a [[France|French]] [[chef]], and winner of the 2007 [[Bocuse d'Or]].<ref name=eb/><ref name=timesbo07>Bremner, Charles. Tourres, Marie. ''The Times'' (January 29, 2007). [http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/europe/article1409196.ece We were whipped by cheat chef, say the losing cooks]</ref> Desvignes is a second chef at the Présidence du Sénat in [[Paris]].<ref name=eb>Bjørn, Else, ''AOKK.dk'' (January 2007). [http://www.aok.dk/byen-rundt/else-bjoerns-noter-og-nyt-fra-januar-2007 Else Bjørns noter og nyt fra januar 2007] {{da_icon}}</ref>

Desvignes’s prize-winning dish was a ''volaille de Bresse truffée'' (truffled Bresse chicken). During the course of the contest, a late delivery of two metal containers to Desvignes became the subject of controversy, with allegations made of cheating by smuggling precooked ingredients into the final.<ref name=timesbo07/> A contest director responded that the containers were delivered to Desvignes two minutes before he started work because snow delayed their overnight arrival, and these contained [[Cutlery|silverware]] and ''[[foie gras]]'', which were not prohibited.<ref name=timesbo07/>

