'''John Cavanagh''' is an [[Americans|American]] economist. He has been the Director of the [[Institute for Policy Studies]] in [[Washington, D.C.]] since 1998, and is a founding fellow of the [[Transnational Institute]] (TNI) in Amsterdam.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.tni.org/users/john-cavanagh|title = John Cavanagh bio|date = |accessdate = 16 October 2014|website = tni.org|publisher = [[Transnational Institute]]|last = |first = }}</ref>

==Career==
{{BLP sources section|date=November 2013}}
Cavanagh has a BA from [[Dartmouth College]] and an MA from [[Princeton University|Princeton]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ips-dc.org/staff/johnc |title=John Cavanagh bio |date= |accessdate=16 October 2014 |website=ips-dc.org |publisher=[[Institute for Policy Studies]] |last= |first= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131121224346/http://www.ips-dc.org/staff/johnc |archivedate=November 21, 2013 }}</ref>

He has worked as an international economist for the [[United Nations Conference on Trade and Development]] (1978-1981) and the [[World Health Organization]] (1981-1982). He directed IPS's Global Economy Project from 1983-1997. Cavanagh helped establish the [[International Forum on Globalisation]] in 1995, and has been active in the anti-[[North American Free Trade Agreement]] networks.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}}

He works closely with the Progressive Caucus of the [[US Congress]] and the international department of the US trade union federation, the AFL-CIO, on [[corporate accountability]] and [[international labour rights]].{{citation needed|date=November 2013}}

Cavanagh currently sits on the board of directors of the [[International Forum on Globalization]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ifg.org/about/bodbios.html#johnbio |title=IFG BOARD OF DIRECTORS BIOS |date= |accessdate=16 October 2014 |website=ifg.org |publisher=[[International Forum on Globalization]] |last= |first= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130128183125/http://ifg.org/about/bodbios.html#johnbio |archivedate=January 28, 2013 }}</ref>

==Works==
He is the co-author of 10 books and numerous articles on [[globalisation]].{{citation needed|date=November 2013}}

